ADR-08 — Use Audit Logging as a Cross-Cutting Concern
Status: Accepted
Context
The CMS requires complete traceability of complaint lifecycle events.
Decision
Create an AuditLog model + AuditLogService to record:
•	complaint creation
•	assignment
•	updates
•	status changes
•	authentication events (optional)
Rationale
•	Supports transparency, accountability, and governance.
•	Required for operational monitoring.
Consequences
Positive: Strong traceability.
Negative: Requires careful logging granularity.
